<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Serena Williams booked her place in the US Open semi-final with a 4-6, 6-3, 6-2 victory over Tsvetana Pironkova.</p>

<p>The six-time champion dropped the first set in the last eight tie with the unseeded Bulgarian claiming an unlikely 6-4 win.</p>

<p>Prionkova then broke Williams in the first game of the second set but the American fought back and found the break at 3-3 to give her the advantage for a 6-3 win and force the match into a deciding set.</p>

<p>A ruthless third set for Williams saw her break early on before her comfortable serving and another break in the seventh handed her the victory and progression to the semi-final. </p>

<p>More to follow. </p>

